{"key":"processedPost-8565823","value":{"id":8565823,"first":8565783,"last":8566753,"when":1214490367,"utime":"06/26/08 05:26 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />What can my FOAF do to their setup to get it to work without the risk of comtams? Or maybe a fully auto.<br /></blockquote><br /><br />I've never yet seen an 'automated' terrarium that would work.&nbsp; Nothing will completely prevent contamination, but fresh swirling air is the best prevention.<br /><br />You won't get that in a sealed terrarium with an air pump.&nbsp; CO2 is 'slightly' heavier than air, so the air from&nbsp; your air pump goes to the top and out, but the CO2 which is the real enemy stays put for the most part.<br /><br />I recommend the <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Terrarium-Tek\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">shotgun type terrarium</a>, but even with this design, a few fannings each day will go a long way towards contaminant prevention.<br />RR","title":"Re: Any luck with Perlite PMP's as an automated FC anyone?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}